EXTRACTED VALUE: Even with the minor warts, Rainbow Six Vegas 2 still provides a great experience, both on and offline. And that's what we all want from our "sequels."
It's Ninja Gaiden II, literally in every sense of the word. It doesn't break any real new ground, but on the other hand, does it really need to?
Impressive, that is all we got to say. Go grab this one before the AAA titles start raining on us this fall.
